"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-brazil-vs-spain-2024-paris-olympics-women-s-soccer-group-stage-live-stream-lineups-preview\", \"text\": \"Though ithasn't been straightforward, the defending world champions, Spain, have booked a ticket into the 2024 Olympic quarterfinals with one group stage match remaining. The Olympic debutant's opponent ahead of the knockouts, Brazil, heads into Wednesday after a devastating result in which it lost a one goal lead in stoppage time to a resilient Japan side.  Even with the gut-punch, the potential of this being Marta's final Olympic match is enough for the Brazilians to rally. There is a lot on the line for the South American powerhouse, who has not finished in the top-six of a major tournament since the 2016 Olympics. Is Arthur Elias under pressure? Maybe, but you can not ignore the consistent failure of this team in competitions not organized by CONMEBOL.  The defeat to the Japanese was the first time in 2024 that As Canarinhas conceded multiple goals in a 90-minute match. They will hope that this defensive record can help propel this team to at least a draw against probably the most technically gifted team in international women's football.  IT ALL STARTS WITH MARTA as she plays a beautiful through ball to Ludmila, who finds 22-year-old Jheniffer to give Brazil the lead \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00a7\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b7 \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00aa\\u0084\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u00a5@TelemundoSportspic.twitter.com/5hLRN1OgqC  Spain, along with the United States, are the only teams through two matchdays with six points. Montserrat Tom\\u00c3\\u00a9's team has held at least 75 percent possession in both of its games, all while recording the most shots of anyone at the Olympics to date (39). Defensively, Spain has allowed just one goal and nine total shots, the fewest of any nation through 180 minutes of football.  The midfield group that includes Teresa Abelleira, 2023 Ballon d'Or F\\u00c3\\u00a9minin winner Aitana Bonmat\\u00c3\\u00ad, and Alexia Putellas has stood out and then some. Putellas, the goal scorer against Nigeria, was exceptional in the double 10 alongside Bonmat\\u00c3\\u00ad last time out. The FC Barcelona star recorded six shots on frame, three key passes, and an 85 percent pass completion percentage.  In competitive world competitions, the two outfits met once \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 2015 Women's World Cup group stage \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Spain's first appearance in the most prestigious football tournament in the world. A goal just before halftime by nowHouston Dash midfielder Andressa Alveswas the difference between the sides.  Goalkeeper:\\u00c2\\u00a0LorenaDefenders:\\u00c2\\u00a0Rafaelle, Tarciane, Tha\\u00c3\\u00ads da SilvaMidfielders:\\u00c2\\u00a0Duda Sampaio, Yasmim, Ana Vit\\u00c3\\u00b3ria, Ant\\u00c3\\u00b4niaForwards:\\u00c2\\u00a0Ludmila, Marta (C), Gabi Nunes  Goalkeeper:Cata CollDefenders:Irene Paredes (C), Oihane Hern\\u00c3\\u00a1ndez, Laia Aleixandri, Ona BatlleMidfielders:Patricia Guijarro, Aitana Bonmat\\u00c3\\u00ad, Teresa AbelleiraForwards:Athenea del Castillo, Salma Paralluelo, Mariona Caldentey  Date:\\u00c2\\u00a0Wednesday, July 31Start time:\\u00c2\\u00a011:00 a.m. ETLocation:\\u00c2\\u00a0Bordeaux, FranceStadium:\\u00c2\\u00a0Nouveau Stade de BordeauxTV Info:\\u00c2\\u00a0NBC Sports App | TelemundoLive Stream:\\u00c2\\u00a0Peacock |\\u00c2FuboTV  Score Prediction:Brazil 1-2 Spain  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026Minute Media-All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Minute Media or its affiliates and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"